      • setPaymentDefault

        @Deprecated
public T setPaymentDefault(long paymentAmount)
        Deprecated. use setPaymentAmount(long) instead.
        Explicitly specify that the operator account is paying for the query and set payment with the given amount.

        Only takes effect if payment is required, has not been set yet, and an operator ID was provided to the Client used to construct this instance.

        Returns:
        this for fluent usage.

      • setPaymentAmount

        public T setPaymentAmount(Hbar paymentAmount)
        Explicitly specify that the operator account is paying for the query; when the query is executed a payment transaction will be constructed with a transfer of this amount from the operator account to the node which will handle the query.
        Returns:
        this for fluent usage.
